lem. Because if it's too much to ask for, you don't care, am I right?<br><br><br><br>&quot;...and that hurts us as a whole.&quot;<br><br>I'm not sure that it does. I'm not at all sure that the &quot;masses&quot; as you call them, aren't better off with the mushroom treatment. Let them confine their energies to playing with TV remotes and voting in presidential elections. If they haven't the fortitude to educate themselves, then I don't want them fucking up the program. I'm not interested in setting up Bill Cosby-style Picture Pages so that halfwits and morons can take part in things like foreign relations and long-term strategic planning.<br><br><br><br>&quot;I'd much rather be given the least amount of bullshit as possible, and that's what I'm arguing for.&quot;<br><br>Yes, I know what you'd rather be given. I'd rather be given blowjobs by the entire cast of the Sports Illustrated swimsuit issue. Would you remove all adversity from your life? No bullies to kick sand in your face? <br><br>How will you develop courage if you are never frightened? How will you become self-reliant if you never have to rely on yourself? How will you come to think for yourself when others always do the thinking for you?<br><br>How will you come to understand ambiguity when the truth is always apparent?<br><br>I'd like to be able to keep my pecs without going to the gym every other day, Gladetree, but you don't see me whining about it. You, on the other hand, seem to feel that you're entitled to be GIVEN &quot;the truth&quot; without so much as an ounce of effort.<br><br>I disagree. I think you should have to exercise that lump of putty between your ears. I think if you won't do it, then you deserve exactly what you get.<br><br>Vanilla, baby. Open wide.<br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulurikeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lurikeen</A></spa